reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good for babies
reviews.reviewText: The ELBEBE Silicone Baby Soft Food Feeding Bottles arrived promptly and in excellent condition, which was a positive start. These bottles are relatively straightforward to clean and function as anticipated. However, they have a notably soft construction, and the nipple size seemed a bit on the smaller side for our 8-month-old baby. It's worth noting that these bottles might be more suitable for younger infants, given the softness and nipple size. While they didn't quite meet our needs for an older baby, they still served their purpose and were functional. Overall, they might be a good choice for those with younger infants.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice feeding bottles
reviews.reviewText: These will probably take some practice to figure out which types of food to use with these. Applesauce might work well with the bigger nipple if it's thinner. Baby food should work, but if you are trying baby led weaning you're probably not using baby food or purees.These bottles are super squishy. That makes them easy to hold, but they do squish more as baby sucks on them so it may be difficult to get all of the food when eating.I think the larger nipple might actually work well with a toddler who's learning to use a cup. They aren't spill proof though.The smaller nipple would work better with liquid than food.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Many people are confused on what these are for, just read the other reviews, and the product description isn't really much help. These are squeeze bottles. They are meant to be used with a thicker consistency: baby cereal, baby purees, baby smoothies. They really aren't meant for infants. They honestly could be dangerous for them due to the flow rate. They have two nipples a criss cross and a circle, the latter has a higher flow rate. They are soft enough to squeeze to increase flow. These are similar to the yogurt/apples sauce pouches but they are reusable and made from silicone.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 25, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I love that these are BPA Free and that it is food safe for the child. The silicone is soft which makes it easy for little hands to hold. Can be cleaned with soap and water or by putting them in the dishwasher. These will make it easy for infants and toddlers to transition from bottles to sippy cups.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good for young toddlers
reviews.reviewText: This wasn't a hit with our infant, probably due to the nipple size and shape. However, they do work great for our young toddler - who can easily hold bottles on their own and likes to squeeze it to make it go faster as well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice feeding bottles
reviews.reviewText: These are pretty nice self feeding bottles. I find that they work best for giving my infant water to drink. The suction is a bit small for a baby that eatss alot.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 19, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Not a bottle that I’d used with my newborn, even though the silicone is soft, the quality is not the best. When my child is able to hold it without assistance, then yes, they have handle to help the smooth transition from baby bottles to sippy cup.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 7, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I think these are better for toddlers than using as baby bottles since the opening on one of the nipples is so big! These silicone bottles are super soft and easy to grip. They are easy to clean as well.
